      "_id": "iwh1nXRZiEujji1N",
      "name": "Breath of Death",
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
      "data": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>The Black Monk exhales a 30-foot cone of tomb gas, <em data-visibility=\"gm\">that deals [[/r 15d6 # negative damage]] negative damage</em> <strong>Basic Saving Throw</strong> <span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"reflex\" data-pf2-traits=\"death,divine,necromancy,negative,damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Breath of Death DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"34\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Reflex</span>. <em data-visibility=\"gm\">A creature that is killed by this negative damage rises [[/gmr 1d4 # rounds later ]] rounds later as a zombie under the control of the Black Monk. It gains the undead trait, retains the abilities it had in life, hit points and a weakness to slashing damage appropriate to its level. The Black Monk can't use Breath of Death again for 1d4 rounds.<br /><br />@Macro[lUHwCzZrLst9sLwX]{Add Breath Weapon Delay}</em></p>"
